"&#xa0;\nWritten evidence from National Task Force (WRT 019)&#xa0;A. Summary&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nB. Context&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nC. 2011 Transport Select Committee Report recommendations and industry response&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nD. Your Questions&#xa0;Question One - How resilient are the UK’s transport networks (including road, rail and air) to adverse winter weather?&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nAdverse weather\n - weather that is bad but not unusual\n. In winter the definitions include more than 2cm of snow in \nLondon\n and the southeast or 5cm elsewhere with a warning about accumulation or drift risk, 60mph winds or temperatures below -3ºC. \nAll\n normal\n years have periods of adverse weather. \nDuring adverse weather the \nindustry plans to run a full service but punctuality may be a fe\nw PPM points lower than \non a normal day\n;\n&#xa0;\nExtreme weather\n - rare weather that is seen once every ten or twenty years\n. In winter this is defined as more than 15cm snow, 70mph winds and temperatures below -7\n \nºC. \nDuring extreme weather the industry seeks to ensure all\n \ncustomer journeys are completed safely\n, and punctuality is not prioritised. \n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nFigure 1: Delay minutes due to winter weather on the third rail network\n \n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;&#xa0;\nQuestion Two - What lessons have been learned since the severe weather experienced in the winter of 2009-10? What practical changes have been made to ensure the UK is now better equipped to deal with severe weather?&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\ni\n. Understand\n \n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nii Eradicate\n \n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nInfrastructure\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nFleet \n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nFigure 2\n: Winter and Autumn performance\n&#xa0;\nFigure 3\n: Winter and autumn performance\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\niii Mitigate\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nFreight\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\niv. \nPlanning for the future\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;Question three - How well prepared are the Government, local authorities and transport providers for adverse winter weather? What more should be done to ensure a coordinated response?&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nE. Conclusions&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nOctober 2013\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n"